# Cloudflare Tunnel configuration for ClusterOS
#
# Setup (one-time, in the Cloudflare dashboard):
#
# There are TWO different values — do not mix them up:
#
#   TUNNEL TOKEN  — long base64 string (~200 chars), used for authentication below.
#                   From: Zero Trust → Tunnels → clusteros → "Install connector" page,
#                   the string after "cloudflared service install ".
#
#   TUNNEL ID     — short UUID (~36 chars, e.g. 6ff42ae2-765d-4e88-9153-b84c10e30b7f),
#                   used ONLY for the DNS CNAME records, NOT pasted below.
#                   From: Zero Trust → Tunnels → click "clusteros" → shown in the detail page.
#
# Steps:
#   1. Go to https://one.dash.cloudflare.com → Networks → Tunnels → Create a tunnel
#      - Type: Cloudflared  |  Name: clusteros  |  Save
#   2. On "Install connector": copy the TUNNEL TOKEN → paste as CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_TOKEN below
#   3. Click the tunnel name to open the detail page → note the TUNNEL ID (UUID)
#   4. In Cloudflare DNS for your domain, add two CNAMEs using the TUNNEL ID:
#        Name: *    Target: <tunnel-UUID>.cfargotunnel.com   (Proxied on)
#        Name: @    Target: <tunnel-UUID>.cfargotunnel.com   (Proxied on)
#      The target will be ~53 chars total — well within the 64-char limit.
#
# Then copy this file to patch/cloudflare.env, fill in the two values below,
# and run: make deploy
#
# Services exposed (once deployed):
#   https://rmatool.org.uk             → landing page
#   https://longhorn.rmatool.org.uk    → Longhorn storage UI
#   https://rancher.rmatool.org.uk     → Rancher cluster manager
#   https://slurm.rmatool.org.uk       → SLURM dashboard + REST API
#   https://jupyter.rmatool.org.uk     → JupyterHub

CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_DOMAIN=rmatool.org.uk
